1. Show all databases
SHOW DATABASES;


2. Create a new database
CREATE DATABASE college;


3. Use (or continue with) a database
USE college;


4. Show all tables in the current database
SHOW TABLES;


5. See the structure of a table
DESC student;


6. View all data inside a table
SELECT * FROM student;


7. Delete or drop a database
DROP DATABASE college;


8. If you want to create a database with the same name again
CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS college;

9. Check which database youâ€™re currently using
SELECT DATABASE();

10. Rename a database (indirect way)
CREATE DATABASE new_name;
USE old_name;
SHOW TABLES;
-- then export or recreate tables in new_name manually if needed
